The paper deals with the construction of random hypergraphs for use in hashing-based data structures, which is a topic in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also makes use of concepts from information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) in its analysis. The use of spatial coupling is a technique commonly used in coding theory (cs.CC) and the paper also employs numerical analysis (cs.NA) in its simulations.
